Scangroup of Kenya Rallies For a Third Day on Report of African Expansion

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-04-21T13:00:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/scangroup-of-kenya-rallies-for-third-day-on-expansion-report.html
Scangroup Ltd., East  Africa ’s
biggest marketing company by sales, rose for a third day after
Reuters reported it plans to expand operations into four African
nations.  Scangroup shares gained 3.5 shillings, or 6.25 percent, to
59.5 shillings by the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi, the capital.
That’s the highest since Feb. 24.  The company plans to buy four businesses in Africa in the
next three years and set up a new operation through its
advertising unit, Reuters reported yesterday, citing Chief
Executive Officer Bharat Thakrar.  Scangroup plans to expand in Nigeria, Ghana, Mozambique and
an unidentified French-speaking African nation, Thakrar told the
 news agency .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
